Retention remains coarse-grained lifecycle management rather than compaction.

Implementation guardrails:
- only whole rolled segments are eligible for deletion
- active-head bytes and retained records are never rewritten in place
- replay now starts from the retained frontier but preserved records remain append-only with original offsets

Focused proof:
- `cargo test -p transit-core retention`

Observed result:
- retained history remains immutable; retention only advances the earliest replayable offset
